02/07/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The OSCE Mission to Croatia issued a statement Friday (2 July) saying mission chief Peter Semneby will release the latest report on Croatia next week.
The analysis will be presented at a press conference Tuesday.
Two days later, it will be submitted to the OSCE Permanent Council in Vienna.
The document assesses the achievements and issues tackled by the mission since December, in line with its mandate.
These include the return of refugees, legislative reform, reform of the media, administration of justice, rule of law, reform of the police, and work with NGOs.
(OSCE Press Release - 02/07/04)
